# TryHackMe — Offensive Security Intro  
**Author:** CyberCitadelSec  
**Date:** Day X  

## 🧠 Overview  
This room introduced the mindset of an ethical hacker and demonstrated how attackers find weaknesses before defenders do.

## 🔍 Key Concepts Learned  
- Offensive security = acting like an attacker  
- Finding hidden pages  
- Understanding admin panels  
- Thinking like a hacker to identify vulnerabilities  

## 🛠️ Skills Practiced  
- Navigating a simulated environment  
- Discovering hidden URLs  
- Interacting with a vulnerable web app  
- Triggering a flag through a money transfer exploit  

## 📌 Summary  
This was my first hands-on hacking room. It taught me how attackers think and how vulnerabilities can be exploited through hidden functionality.

## 🎯 Next Room  
Linux Fundamentals Part 1
